<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-02T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-02T07:00:00-05:00" n="319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/7545</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-02T13:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 2, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 3, 9.10
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1171. Situation unchanged, only more news coming of Second Army’s
                                going on strike and declaring for peace with exception of certain
                                units that fought till extirpated. All depends whether the <pb facs="0361" n="287" xml:id="pg_287"/> insidious propaganda based
                                on socialists’ literature and the Pope’s peace suggestions have
                                undermined other forces, especially Third Army on which rest hopes
                                of immediate defense and time for reorganization. If Italy can
                                reorganize promptly Second Army, the disaster not irremediable
                                because the Allies are rushing in troops. At present Italians
                                reported holding part of the Tagliamento line though believe that
                                they are falling back on Piave line. British and French will require
                                perhaps fortnight to get in action in force. British Chief of Staff
                                    <persName corresp="#p_RSW1">Robertson</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_FGF1">General Foch</persName> are here to-day
                                canvassing situation. Intention is to try for the present to hold
                                Venice; all depends on Italy’s power to keep up fight. Little
                                information given out but people so far calm and firm.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>